cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CG 

This paper deals with discrete energy minimization problems, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of these problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
